frameDefinitions: This frame involves a static (primarily spatial) relationship between a Location and a Theme, in which the Theme is located in many or all subregions of the Location, and is thus construable as covering it.
A Location is characterized by a high amount of (often goal-oriented)
These are words relating to filling containers and covering areas with some thing, things or substance, the Theme.
A Questioner asks a Witness (or defendant) questions in the context of a court procedure.
In this frame a Patient is in a state of having been broken into smaller pieces.  '
A Location is filled or covered with the Theme.
frameExamples: Lionel Hutz <t>coated</t> the wall with paint.
We 'd like to <t>cross-examine</t> the witness if we can.
The waters of the bay <t>teemed</t> with fish.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Theme</fen> in this frame is the object which is described as standing in some spatial relation to a particular <fen>Location</fen>.  <fen>Theme</fen> typically occurs as the External Argument or, with passives, as a PP Complement headed by 'with' or 'by'.
<fen>Location</fen> is the entity or area with respect to which the <fen>Theme</fen>'s spatial arrangement is described.  This frame element generally occurs as an NP Object.
The time at which the <fen>Theme</fen> occupies the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Location</fen> where a lot of activity is taking place, or prototypically takes place.
The <fen>Activity</fen> that is conceptually filling the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Individuals</fen> are engaged in the <fen>Activity</fen>, creating a lively <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Location</fen> is characterized by a lot of activity.
The larger or general area where the <fen>Location</fen> is lively.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the actor who instigates the filling.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the physical object or substance which changes location.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is the area or container being filled. Goal is generally the NP Object in this frame.
An event which brings about the filling of the <fen>Goal</fen>.
When the filling occurs.
Where the filling takes place.
The individual who asks a <fen>Witness</fen> questions.
A person who is present in a courtroom in order to give some form of evidence, has been sworn in, and is being examined by a <fen>Questioner</fen>.
When the examination occurs.
Where the examination takes place.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity acted on and that undergoes a change.
The <fen>Theme</fen> covers or fills the <fen>Location</fen>.  This role most frequently occurs in a PP Complement headed by with or in.
<fen>Location</fen> is the object or area that the <fen>Theme</fen> fills or covers.  This frame element generally occurs as the External Argument.
The period of time during which the the Abounding_with event occurs.
listRoleExamples: <fex>On this side of town</fex> the streets are livelier.
Rev. Lovejoy carefully brushed the rolls <fex>with butter</fex>.
You have leave to examine <fex>the witness.</fex>
The waters of the bay teemed <fex>with fish</fex>.
<fex>The walls</fex> crawled with nanite surveillance probes.
